# Clerk Billing — Plans, Features & Access Control

This app uses **Clerk Billing (B2C)** for subscriptions and payments. Plans and Features are configured in the [Clerk Dashboard](https://dashboard.clerk.com/~/billing/plans). Gate premium functionality server-side; use client `<Show>` only for UI visibility.

> Billing is in Beta — pin Clerk SDK and `clerk-js` versions to avoid breaking API changes.

## Plans & Features (this app)

| Plan slug     | Features                                              |
|---------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| `free_user`   | `3_deck_limit` — user may create **at most 3 decks** |
| `pro`         | `unlimited_decks`, `ai_flashcard_generation`         |

Use **Feature** checks for entitlements (preferred). Use **Plan** checks when gating entire tiers.

```typescript
// Feature checks (preferred)
has({ feature: "unlimited_decks" })
has({ feature: "3_deck_limit" })          // free tier — enforce deck count cap
has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" })

// Plan checks
has({ plan: "free_user" })
has({ plan: "pro" })
```

## Server-side access — `has()` (required for enforcement)

In Server Components, Server Actions, and Route Handlers, destructure `has` from `auth()` alongside `userId`. Never rely on client-only checks to allow mutations or data access.

```typescript
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { userId, has } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

// ✅ Deck creation — enforce free tier limit server-side
const canCreateUnlimited = has({ feature: "unlimited_decks" });
if (!canCreateUnlimited) {
  const deckCount = await getDeckCountByUser(userId);
  if (deckCount >= 3) throw new Error("Deck limit reached. Upgrade to Pro.");
}

// ✅ AI flashcard generation — pro feature only
if (!has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" })) {
  throw new Error("AI generation requires a Pro subscription.");
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — gating mutations only in the client
"use client";
if (!userHasPro) createDeck(...);
```

Combine with [clerk-auth.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/clerk-auth.mdc): always derive `userId` from `auth()`, never from the client.

## Client UI — `<Show>` component

Use `<Show>` from `@clerk/nextjs` to show/hide UI (upgrade prompts, Pro buttons). Always provide a `fallback` for locked content.

```tsx
import { Show } from "@clerk/nextjs";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

<Show
  when={{ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" }}
  fallback={<Button variant="outline" asChild><Link href="/pricing">Upgrade to Pro</Link></Button>}
>
  <GenerateWithAIButton />
</Show>
```

```tsx
<Show
  when={{ plan: "pro" }}
  fallback={<p>Pro subscribers only.</p>}
>
  <ProOnlyContent />
</Show>
```

## Pricing page

Use Clerk's `<PricingTable />` on a dedicated pricing route. Wrap layout with shadcn/Tailwind — do not use raw inline styles.

```tsx
// app/pricing/page.tsx
import { PricingTable } from "@clerk/nextjs";

export default function PricingPage() {
  return (
    <div className="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-8">
      <PricingTable />
    </div>
  );
}
```

Sign-in/up triggers must remain shadcn `<Button>` + Clerk modal per [shadcn-ui.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/shadcn-ui.mdc).

## Where to enforce what

| Capability              | Feature to check              | Enforce in                          |
|-------------------------|-------------------------------|-------------------------------------|
| Create deck (≤3 free)   | `unlimited_decks` or count    | Server Action before insert         |
| Unlimited decks         | `unlimited_decks`             | Server Action before insert         |
| AI flashcard generation | `ai_flashcard_generation`   | Server Action + hide UI with `<Show>` |

Free users implicitly have `3_deck_limit` via the `free_user` plan — check `unlimited_decks` to skip the cap, or verify deck count when the feature is absent.
